<section id="fs-id1198403" class="section-summary"><title>Section Summary</title><list id="fs-id3080578"><item id="import-auto-id2438220">Density is the mass per unit volume of a substance or object. In equation form, density is defined as
        <equation id="eip-291"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>ρ</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mi>V</m:mi></m:mfrac></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></equation></item>
            <item id="import-auto-id1588322">The SI unit of density is <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mtext>kg/m</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow></m:math>.</item>
    </list></section><section id="fs-id2677348" class="conceptual-questions" type="conceptual-questions"><title>Conceptual Questions</title>
